256
00:22:32,601 --> 00:22:34,852
Hey, listen, Maggie. Thank you for everything.

257
00:22:34,936 --> 00:22:36,520
You're a real pal.

258
00:22:36,897 --> 00:22:38,022
Oh, yeah?

259
00:22:38,106 --> 00:22:40,858
Yeah, yeah. Give Andy a kiss for me, will you?

260
00:22:40,942 --> 00:22:42,318
See you soon. Bye.

261
00:23:21,066 --> 00:23:22,942
What is wrong with me?

262
00:23:23,568 --> 00:23:25,945
I'm scaring myself half to death.

263
00:23:56,184 --> 00:23:57,935
POLICEMAN 1: Step away from this barricade.

264
00:23:58,019 --> 00:24:00,855
Come on, move it back. There's nothing to see.

265
00:24:00,939 --> 00:24:02,940
POLICEMAN 2: Now, let's move this police line back here.

266
00:24:03,024 --> 00:24:05,025
Go on home, folks, please.

267
00:24:16,204 --> 00:24:18,289
DETECTIVE: She was on the sixth floor.

268
00:24:29,468 --> 00:24:31,385
Miss, what do you think you're doing?

269
00:24:31,470 --> 00:24:32,887
I live here.

270
00:24:39,394 --> 00:24:40,519
Andy?

271
00:24:42,230 --> 00:24:44,315
Oh, no. Andy?

272
00:24:45,901 --> 00:24:47,026
Andy?

273
00:24:47,944 --> 00:24:49,236
Andy!

274
00:24:49,321 --> 00:24:50,488
Mommy!

275
00:24:51,239 --> 00:24:52,781
Oh, thank God.

276
00:24:53,950 --> 00:24:55,618
Are you all right?

277
00:24:55,744 --> 00:24:58,370
Oh, I'm so glad. I got so scared when I...

278
00:24:58,455 --> 00:25:00,706
What's wrong? Where's Maggie?

279
00:25:01,208 --> 00:25:03,417
She had an accident.

280
00:25:03,502 --> 00:25:05,169
Accident? What kind of an accident?

281
00:25:05,253 --> 00:25:08,380
Mrs. Barclay, I'm Detective Mike Norris, Homicide.

282
00:25:08,465 --> 00:25:10,549
Could I talk to you out in the hall?

283
00:25:10,634 --> 00:25:12,009
Why? What's happened to Maggie?

284
00:25:12,093 --> 00:25:13,385
Please?

285
00:25:15,680 --> 00:25:17,431
I'll be right back.

286
00:25:25,732 --> 00:25:27,483
Look, Mrs. Barclay...

287
00:25:34,783 --> 00:25:35,908
What?

288
00:25:36,535 --> 00:25:38,118
Miss Peterson's dead, Mrs. Barclay.

289
00:25:38,203 --> 00:25:39,370
What?

290
00:25:42,457 --> 00:25:43,499
How?

291
00:25:43,583 --> 00:25:45,292
She fell from your kitchen window.

292
00:25:45,794 --> 00:25:47,294
Oh, no.

293
00:25:49,881 --> 00:25:51,423
You all right?

294
00:25:52,425 --> 00:25:53,842
Yes. All right.

295
00:25:54,135 --> 00:25:55,386
Come on.

296
00:25:59,933 --> 00:26:01,392
Oh, Maggie.

297
00:26:01,935 --> 00:26:03,394
Did you check over here?

298
00:26:06,982 --> 00:26:08,315
Oh, Maggie.

299
00:26:13,154 --> 00:26:15,489
You got any idea what these are?

300
00:26:20,579 --> 00:26:21,662
No.

301
00:26:22,122 --> 00:26:25,916
MIKE: They look like footprints, don't they? Very small footprints.

302
00:26:26,835 --> 00:26:28,669
What are you implying?

303
00:26:29,087 --> 00:26:30,629
I don't know.

304
00:26:30,714 --> 00:26:32,590
What would Andy be doing up on the counter, right?

305
00:26:32,674 --> 00:26:33,632
- What?
- Besides,

306
00:26:33,717 --> 00:26:37,303
I already checked his closet. None of his shoes matched these prints.

307
00:26:37,387 --> 00:26:40,306
Mommy? Mommy?

308
00:26:40,390 --> 00:26:43,350
Chucky wanted to know what was going on.

309
00:26:43,435 --> 00:26:44,476
Andy, I want you to go to bed.

310
00:26:44,561 --> 00:26:46,103
The detective and I are very busy.

311
00:26:46,187 --> 00:26:47,229
But, Mom...

312
00:26:47,314 --> 00:26:48,731
Right now, please.

313
00:26:50,859 --> 00:26:52,026
MIKE: Andy.

314
00:26:52,694 --> 00:26:54,528
What do you got on your feet?

315
00:26:55,447 --> 00:26:58,282
Good Guy PJ sneakers.

316
00:26:58,366 --> 00:27:00,284
Wow. Come here.

317
00:27:03,038 --> 00:27:04,455
Can I see the bottoms of them?

318
00:27:04,539 --> 00:27:05,706
Sure.

319
00:27:06,708 --> 00:27:09,960
Look at this. There's a gun. Is that a cowboy hat?

320
00:27:10,045 --> 00:27:13,213
Andy, get into bed. I'll be in in a minute to tuck you in.

321
00:27:13,298 --> 00:27:15,215
- But, Mom...
- Right now.

322
00:27:20,805 --> 00:27:22,640
Why are you treating Andy like this?

323
00:27:22,724 --> 00:27:26,268
If he says he doesn't know how those footprints got there, then he doesn't.

324
00:27:26,353 --> 00:27:28,312
Look, Mrs. Barclay, somebody made those footprints.

325
00:27:28,396 --> 00:27:29,396
If not Andy, then who?

326
00:27:29,481 --> 00:27:31,440
I don't know, and I don't care.

327
00:27:31,524 --> 00:27:34,360
All I know is that I've just lost my best friend tonight to a horrible accident

328
00:27:34,444 --> 00:27:35,944
and I would like some time alone with my son,

329
00:27:36,029 --> 00:27:38,113
who I'm sure is just as upset about this as I am.

330
00:27:38,198 --> 00:27:40,824
Okay. Sorry. I'm sorry.

331
00:27:40,909 --> 00:27:44,078
I'll clear everybody out of here right away. Okay?

332
00:27:44,162 --> 00:27:46,997
Hey, guys, you done? Let's go. Chop-chop.

333
00:27:47,082 --> 00:27:49,208
Let's go, everybody. Out of here.

334
00:27:49,292 --> 00:27:51,168
POLICEMAN 1: Let's clear this up over here. Come on.

335
00:27:51,252 --> 00:27:52,336
POLICEMAN 2: Okay.

336
00:27:52,420 --> 00:27:54,088
POLICEMAN 3: Let's go, Sid.

337
00:27:59,552 --> 00:28:04,473
What do you think was so important about my sneakers, Chucky?

338
00:28:05,350 --> 00:28:07,893
You don't know either, do you?

339
00:28:28,623 --> 00:28:31,041
Well, let me know if you find out anything about those footprints.

340
00:28:31,126 --> 00:28:32,626
Mommy, Mommy.

341
00:28:32,752 --> 00:28:35,337
Mommy, I know who was on the kitchen counter. I know, I know.

342
00:28:35,422 --> 00:28:37,631
- Andy, I thought I...
- Who, Andy? Who?

343
00:28:37,716 --> 00:28:38,966
Chucky!

344
00:28:39,467 --> 00:28:40,801
Your doll?

345
00:28:41,845 --> 00:28:43,137
KAREN: Andy, that's enough stories for tonight.

346
00:28:43,221 --> 00:28:46,098
Now, come on, back to bed. Now I mean it.

347
00:28:46,182 --> 00:28:47,558
But, Mom...

348
00:28:51,855 --> 00:28:53,731
Good night, Detective.

349
00:28:57,026 --> 00:28:58,610
- What?
- Are you gonna call me?

350
00:28:58,695 --> 00:29:00,112
You don't give up, do you?

351
00:29:00,196 --> 00:29:02,656
I just...I hate loose ends.

352
00:29:02,741 --> 00:29:05,200
And I hate people who don't know when to stop.

353
00:29:06,536 --> 00:29:07,578
Ouch.

354
00:29:07,662 --> 00:29:08,871
A spirited lady.

355
00:29:08,955 --> 00:29:10,330
No kidding.

356
00:29:10,415 --> 00:29:12,040
I want that autopsy report on my desk

357
00:29:12,125 --> 00:29:13,459
- first thing tomorrow.
- Yeah.

358
00:29:13,543 --> 00:29:16,253
And anything you can find out about Mrs. Barclay and her son.

359
00:29:16,337 --> 00:29:19,006
You got it. Anything else I can do for you, sir?

360
00:29:19,090 --> 00:29:22,843
Oh, yeah. Here. Get this to the lab.

361
00:29:22,927 --> 00:29:24,511
I found it in the corner of the kitchen.

362
00:29:24,596 --> 00:29:25,596
What is this?

363
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:27,055
Possible murder weapon.

364
00:29:27,140 --> 00:29:28,140
No.

365
00:29:29,225 --> 00:29:31,351
Come on. You're kidding me.

366
00:29:33,062 --> 00:29:35,606
Hey, you are kidding me, aren't you?

367
00:29:40,361 --> 00:29:43,447
ANDY: 'Cause she saw you walking and talking?

368
00:29:55,877 --> 00:29:59,880
I guess there was no hiding from her.

369
00:30:04,093 --> 00:30:06,011
Andy, who are you talking to?

370
00:30:06,095 --> 00:30:07,304
Chucky.

371
00:30:19,192 --> 00:30:20,609
Chucky, huh?

372
00:30:20,819 --> 00:30:22,736
Yeah, sure, Chucky.

373
00:30:22,821 --> 00:30:25,072
He's sitting right over there.

374
00:30:28,535 --> 00:30:31,411
Chucky's been talking to you, too, hasn't he?

375
00:30:31,496 --> 00:30:32,663
What's he been saying?

376
00:30:32,747 --> 00:30:35,290
All kinds of things.

377
00:30:35,375 --> 00:30:38,794
His real name is Charles Lee Ray,

378
00:30:38,878 --> 00:30:43,966
and he's been sent down from heaven by Daddy to play with me.

379
00:30:48,638 --> 00:30:51,682
He has, has he? Anything else?

380
00:30:52,016 --> 00:30:55,769
Yes. He said Aunt Maggie was a real bitch

381
00:30:55,854 --> 00:30:57,896
and got what she deserved.

382
00:30:58,481 --> 00:31:01,859
Andy, how can you say something so horrible?

383
00:31:02,443 --> 00:31:04,611
I didn't say it. Chucky did.

384
00:31:04,696 --> 00:31:06,321
Andy, stop it.

385
00:31:06,406 --> 00:31:08,782
You know perfectly well that you're making this up.

386
00:31:09,576 --> 00:31:12,661
But I'm not. Chucky's alive. Really, he is.

387
00:31:12,745 --> 00:31:15,747
Andy, Chucky... Chucky's a doll.

388
00:31:16,291 --> 00:31:18,375
He's made of plastic and stuffing.

389
00:31:18,459 --> 00:31:20,002
Look at him. Look at him.

390
00:31:20,086 --> 00:31:22,045
Now, does he look like anything else to you?

391
00:31:22,130 --> 00:31:23,755
Don't, you'll hurt him.

392
00:31:23,840 --> 00:31:25,257
Andy, look!

393
00:31:26,217 --> 00:31:29,511
Now you don't really think that Chucky is alive, do you?

394
00:31:29,596 --> 00:31:31,013
But he is.

395
00:31:31,097 --> 00:31:33,640
Andy, stop it. Please.

396
00:31:34,684 --> 00:31:39,438
It's 'cause of Aunt Maggie you're yelling at me, isn't it?

397
00:31:42,317 --> 00:31:45,777
Yes. Yes, I guess it is.

398
00:31:46,154 --> 00:31:47,821
I'm sorry.

399
00:31:47,906 --> 00:31:50,699
I'll stop making up stories.

400
00:31:56,039 --> 00:31:57,539
Thanks, champ.

401
00:31:59,292 --> 00:32:01,335
Do you wanna sleep in with me tonight?

402
00:32:01,419 --> 00:32:03,378
No, it's all right.

403
00:32:03,796 --> 00:32:05,672
I've got Chucky.

404
00:32:09,385 --> 00:32:11,094
Come on, into bed.

405
00:32:16,476 --> 00:32:18,393
Good night, sweetheart.

406
00:32:20,480 --> 00:32:21,855
I love you.

407
00:32:27,904 --> 00:32:29,029
Good night.

408
00:32:38,539 --> 00:32:42,751
You're right, Chucky. She didn't believe me.

409
00:32:49,634 --> 00:32:51,635
Hi. I like to be hugged.

410
00:32:52,053 --> 00:32:55,973
Good. I'd love to hug you, too.

411
00:33:10,321 --> 00:33:11,530
Hey.

412
00:33:12,323 --> 00:33:14,533
You sure you're all right about last night?

413
00:33:14,617 --> 00:33:16,994
No bad dreams about Aunt Maggie?

414
00:33:17,620 --> 00:33:19,997
And Chucky's only a doll, right?

415
00:33:21,958 --> 00:33:24,835
All right, off to school with you, then. I love you tons.

416
00:34:40,328 --> 00:34:43,371
MAN ON PA: 43rd street. Next stop, 47th.

417
00:35:35,716 --> 00:35:37,342
Is that Eddie's?

418
00:35:41,556 --> 00:35:45,642
Look, you stay here. I have to go tinkle.

419
00:35:56,904 --> 00:35:59,114
I'll be right there, Chucky.

420
00:37:14,190 --> 00:37:17,651
Chucky?

421
00:38:10,162 --> 00:38:23,550
Chucky?

422
00:38:37,565 --> 00:38:44,446
Chucky?

423
00:39:08,262 --> 00:39:09,512
Mrs. Barclay.

424
00:39:09,597 --> 00:39:12,474
Detective Norris, I came as soon as I got your message.

425
00:39:12,558 --> 00:39:14,059
You haven't been to the school to pick up your son yet?

426
00:39:14,143 --> 00:39:16,853
No. No, I came directly from work. Why?

427
00:39:16,937 --> 00:39:18,104
Let's go into my office.

428
00:39:19,690 --> 00:39:20,857
Is something wrong with Andy?

429
00:39:20,941 --> 00:39:22,317
Please.

430
00:39:24,862 --> 00:39:25,945
I...

431
00:39:30,201 --> 00:39:32,285
I don't know how to tell you this, Mrs. Barclay.

432
00:39:32,370 --> 00:39:33,828
Tell me what?

433
00:39:33,913 --> 00:39:37,290
Do you have any idea why your Aunt Maggie fell out of that window?

434
00:39:37,375 --> 00:39:38,541
Yes.

435
00:39:38,626 --> 00:39:40,502
Could you tell me why?

436
00:39:41,128 --> 00:39:46,007
'Cause she saw Chucky, and it scared her so much, she fell out.

437
00:39:46,092 --> 00:39:47,717
Oh, she did, huh?

438
00:39:48,302 --> 00:39:51,137
(DOOR OPENING) So why did Chucky go to see Eddie Caputo?

439
00:39:51,222 --> 00:39:52,472
Mommy!

440
00:39:52,556 --> 00:39:54,182
Oh, Andy.

441
00:39:58,145 --> 00:40:00,438
All right, sweetheart. Come on.

442
00:40:02,691 --> 00:40:04,609
Now listen to me, okay?

443
00:40:05,820 --> 00:40:08,321
Nobody believes you about Chucky.

444
00:40:09,323 --> 00:40:12,200
Unless you start telling the truth right now,

445
00:40:13,661 --> 00:40:16,371
They're going to take you away from me.

446
00:40:18,999 --> 00:40:20,625
You hear that, Chucky?

447
00:40:20,709 --> 00:40:23,837
They're taking me away unless you say something.

448
00:40:26,590 --> 00:40:28,508
Please, say something.

449
00:40:30,094 --> 00:40:32,846
Come on, Chucky. Say something.

450
00:40:32,930 --> 00:40:36,433
Tell me why you lied to me about everything.

451
00:40:36,517 --> 00:40:39,769
Come on, Chucky. Say something.

452
00:40:40,104 --> 00:40:41,688
Tell me.

453
00:40:41,772 --> 00:40:46,276
Hi, I'm Chucky, and I'm your friend to the end. Hidey-ho.

454
00:40:48,779 --> 00:40:51,573
Mommy, he's doing it on purpose.

455
00:40:51,657 --> 00:40:56,035
He told me never to tell about him or he'd kill me.

456
00:40:56,120 --> 00:40:59,873
Mrs. Barclay, my name is Dr. Ardmore. I'm from County General.

457
00:41:00,040 --> 00:41:02,125
I've seen more than enough.

458
00:41:02,418 --> 00:41:05,587
Maybe Andy should spend a couple of days with us.

459
00:41:43,083 --> 00:41:47,504
Well, say something, you little bastard.

460
00:41:49,423 --> 00:41:51,299
Say something, damn it!

461
00:41:52,510 --> 00:41:54,677
Hi. I like to be hugged.

462
00:42:36,470 --> 00:42:38,888
"He wants you for a best friend."

463
00:42:39,181 --> 00:42:40,598
Yeah, sure.

464
00:43:39,908 --> 00:43:41,784
Hi, I'm Chucky. Wanna play?

465
00:44:45,599 --> 00:44:46,974
Talk to me.

466
00:44:48,435 --> 00:44:49,936
Come on, talk.

467
00:44:51,772 --> 00:44:54,399
I said, talk to me, damn it. All right.

468
00:44:55,067 --> 00:44:57,235
Then I'm gonna make you talk!

469
00:45:09,957 --> 00:45:13,710
I said talk to me, damn it, or else I am gonna throw you in the fire!

470
00:45:13,794 --> 00:45:16,462
You stupid bitch! You filthy slut!

471
00:45:16,547 --> 00:45:18,089
I'll teach you to fuck with me!

472
00:45:18,173 --> 00:45:19,382
No! No!

473
00:45:58,172 --> 00:45:59,297
Stop!

474
00:46:33,415 --> 00:46:37,960
No.

475
00:46:41,381 --> 00:46:42,465
No!

476
00:46:52,434 --> 00:46:54,310
Oh, Detective Norris!

477
00:46:54,394 --> 00:46:56,103
Mrs. Barclay, what are you doing back here?

478
00:46:56,188 --> 00:46:57,647
Andy was telling the truth.

479
00:46:57,731 --> 00:47:00,107
Chucky is alive and he killed Eddie Caputo.

480
00:47:00,234 --> 00:47:02,235
- What?
- I took him home to my apartment.

481
00:47:02,319 --> 00:47:06,197
I was about to throw away the box that he came in when the batteries fell out.

482
00:47:06,281 --> 00:47:07,365
Don't you see?

483
00:47:07,449 --> 00:47:10,743
He's been moving and talking for days without any batteries in him.

484
00:47:10,828 --> 00:47:12,036
What are you talking about?

485
00:47:12,120 --> 00:47:13,830
How I found out the doll was alive.

486
00:47:13,914 --> 00:47:16,290
See, I threatened to throw him into the fireplace,

487
00:47:16,375 --> 00:47:18,960
when all of a sudden, he came alive in my hand.

488
00:47:19,044 --> 00:47:22,129
I dropped him, and he got up and ran out of the apartment.

489
00:47:22,923 --> 00:47:24,590
Good night, Mrs. Barclay.

490
00:47:24,675 --> 00:47:27,760
Wait a minute. I am telling you the truth.

491
00:47:27,845 --> 00:47:29,512
He killed Maggie. He killed Eddie Caputo.

492
00:47:29,596 --> 00:47:31,013
Look, Mrs. Barclay.

493
00:47:31,098 --> 00:47:32,932
I sympathize with you. I really do.

494
00:47:33,016 --> 00:47:34,851
I hated what happened in there today.

495
00:47:34,935 --> 00:47:36,644
But lying is not gonna help your son.

496
00:47:36,728 --> 00:47:38,855
Lying? Does this look like I'm lying?

497
00:47:40,691 --> 00:47:41,691
How did you get those?

498
00:47:41,775 --> 00:47:42,942
Chucky bit me.

499
00:47:43,026 --> 00:47:45,778
Oh, for God's sake.

500
00:47:45,863 --> 00:47:48,030
All right, don't believe me.

501
00:47:49,491 --> 00:47:50,533
Where you going?

502
00:47:50,617 --> 00:47:51,951
To find Chucky.

503
00:47:52,035 --> 00:47:53,244
How you gonna do that?

504
00:47:53,328 --> 00:47:55,663
I bought him from a peddler where I work. I'll start there.

505
00:47:55,747 --> 00:47:58,291
That isn't a good part of town to be in at this time of night.

506
00:47:58,709 --> 00:48:00,209
Mrs. Barclay, do you hear me?

507
00:48:00,294 --> 00:48:03,212
You don't want to go down there at this time of night.

508
00:48:07,885 --> 00:48:09,719
God damn it.

509
00:49:08,528 --> 00:49:10,237
Uh-huh.

510
00:49:24,711 --> 00:49:26,545
What's she doing here?

511
00:49:30,550 --> 00:49:32,635
Hey, excuse me.

512
00:49:32,719 --> 00:49:37,974
Mister.

513
00:49:38,100 --> 00:49:40,810
I'm not gonna hurt you. Do you remember me?

514
00:49:40,894 --> 00:49:41,852
No, no.

515
00:49:41,937 --> 00:49:43,062
I'm sorry. I bought a doll from you

516
00:49:43,146 --> 00:49:45,314
in back of Carson's department store with my friend yesterday.

517
00:49:45,399 --> 00:49:47,274
- Doll?
- Yes, a Good Guy doll.

518
00:49:47,359 --> 00:49:49,151
You sold it to me. Do you remember?

519
00:49:49,236 --> 00:49:50,987
Oh, yeah, a doll. What about it?

